The President delivered remarks at the 66th annual National Prayer Breakfast, expressing gratitude for the power of prayer in American life and liberty. He emphasized that faith is central to American values and that the rights of American citizens come from their Creator. The President praised the courage and selflessness of Americans in times of crisis, such as during natural disasters and acts of violence. He also highlighted the importance of religious freedom and expressed support for those suffering from religious persecution around the world. The President mentioned the progress in defeating ISIS and the hope symbolized by a North Korean defector and a young girl who overcame a rare disease. He called on Americans to find the best within themselves and work towards a more just and peaceful world. The President concluded by affirming that as long as America remains true to its founding principles, it will continue to be a beacon of freedom and hope.